import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across budget years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['budgetYear']).mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['value'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average value')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the average value for each budget year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
